The paper deals with the privacy and security of in-vehicle network data captured on the vehicle's CAN bus, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also extensively uses machine learning techniques to extract signals from the CAN logs, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with image processing techniques to extract signals, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the statistical features of signals, which falls under the category of statistics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with the privacy and security of personal data, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
